				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-720bc0b8 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="720bc0b8" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
								<div class="elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix">
				<p>A few weeks after getting hired I was assigned to be a point of contact for two of the larger levels in the game, along with a partner. My responsibilities encompassed making sure the levels were stable with no major bugs, completing test cases to catch large amounts of smaller bugs, as well as completing various passes &amp; other routine checks throughout the week. Additionally I was responsible for responding to any requests/callouts from devs working on the level. This included things such as tweaking nav mesh, tagging object surfaces, or simply just logging a bug someone caught while playing.</p><p>This was an amazing opportunity to work directly with the design team, as well as the people from other departments working on these levels. It was extremely inspiring and educational to get to see some of the best of the best in action.</p><p>Here are the chapters that the two levels encompass:</p>					</div>
						</div>
